title: First trip out of Texas a disaster for Aggies
text:
Photo: Rogelio V. Solis, STF / Associated Press Image 1 of / 1 1 Mississippi running back Akeem Judd (21) dives for extra yards as Texas A&M defensive back Justin Evans (14) closes in to tackle during the first half of an NCAA college football game in Oxford, Miss., Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015. (AP Photo/Rogelio V. Solis) Mississippi running back Akeem Judd (21) dives for extra yards as Texas A&M defensive back Justin Evans (14) closes in to tackle during the first half of an NCAA college football game in Oxford, Miss., ... more First trip out of Texas a disaster for Aggies 1 / 1 Back to Gallery OXFORD, Miss. — Texas A&M and Mississippi played what amounted to an SEC West division elimination game on Saturday night at Vaught-Hemingway Stadium.
Consider the No. 15 Aggies eliminated and browbeaten to boot, following the No. 24 Rebels’ 23-3 victory, A&M’s second straight double-digit setback in conference action following a 5-0 overall start.
